description: This is a market on whether the number of Americans that file weekly jobless claims will exceed 360,000 for the week ending on Saturday, July 17, 2021. This market will resolve to “Yes” if the United States Department of Labor reports that there were more than 360,000 seasonally adjusted initial claims for unemployment insurance for the week ending on July 17, 2021. This market will resolve to “No” if the United States Department of Labor reports that there were 360,000 or less seasonally adjusted initial claims for unemployment insurance for the week ending on July 17, 2021.  The resolution source for this market will be the United States Department of Labor’s Weekly Uninsurance Claims report for the week ending on Saturday, July 17, 2021, expected to be released on Thursday, July 22, 2021, 8:30 AM ET. Resolution of this market will take place upon release of the aforementioned data. If data is not available for the aforementioned dates by Wednesday, July 28, 2021, 12:00 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.
